definitions.definition: Someone advertising for customers in an aggressive way.
examples: Be careful of the ticket touts outside the arena, they are famed for selling counterfeits.

definitions.definition: A person, at a racecourse , who offers supposedly inside information on which horse is likely to win.
( colloquial ) An informer in the Irish Republican Army .
( colloquial , archaic ) A spy for a smuggler , thief , or similar.
